# Code of Conduct – EcoShare Sprint 3

## Communication

* All group members will communicate respectfully and professionally during meetings, labs, and online platforms (e.g., WhatsApp, Teams).
* Messages should be responded to within a reasonable time (within 24 hours where possible).
* Important updates (e.g., missed deadlines, illness) must be communicated clearly to the group.

## Contribution

* All members are expected to contribute fairly to development, testing, documentation, and presentation.
* If a member is unable to complete their task (e.g., due to illness), they must inform the group early so responsibilities can be reassigned.
* Members who were previously unavailable (e.g., sick) should catch up on missed work and contribute to remaining tasks.

## Meetings & Lab Attendance

* Attendance in lab sessions is compulsory as they are essential for project progress.
* Members should attend scheduled group meetings and actively participate.
* If a member misses a lab or meeting, they must:

  * Inform the group in advance (if possible)
  * Review what was covered
  * Complete any missed work independently

## GitHub Usage

* All work must be committed regularly to GitHub with clear commit messages.
* Each member should contribute visible commits to demonstrate their involvement.
* Members should pull the latest version before starting work to avoid conflicts.

## Deadlines & Responsibility

* Tasks should be completed by agreed deadlines.
* If delays occur, members must notify the group as early as possible.
* Last-minute work or lack of contribution may impact group performance and will be addressed.

## Conflict Resolution

* Issues should be discussed calmly and respectfully within the group first.
* If problems continue (e.g., lack of contribution, missed work), they should be documented.
* The module teaching team will be contacted if the issue cannot be resolved internally.

## Professional Conduct

* All members are expected to act responsibly and support each other.
* The group understands that unexpected situations (e.g., illness) can occur, but communication and accountability are essential.
* Everyone is responsible for ensuring the project meets submission and lab requirements.
